{"lemma":"عُقّالٌ","slug":"عُقّالٌ","root":"ع.ق.ل","root_slug":"ع-ق-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ق-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29984","n29988"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8F%D9%82%D9%91%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"reasonable, endowed with reason, prudent"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"rational, intelligent, sentient"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"of sound mind, compos mentis"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"entitled to an inheritance"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"used in reference to animate beings that are perceived as capable of thinking such as humans and angels"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of عَقَلَ (ʕaqala, “to be endowed with reason, to have intelligence, to be conscious, to realize”)."},"ipa":["/ʕaː.qil/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29984","headword_ar":"عِقَالٌ","root":"Eql","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rope with which a camel's fore shank is bound to his arm, both being folded together and bound in the middle of the arm:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqulN","text_ar":"عُقُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O, Msb.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ikaAlN","text_ar":"شِكَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poor-rate"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a year,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consisting of camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [See a verse cited in the first paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sEw","text_ar":"سعو"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sEY","text_ar":"سعى"},{"kind":"text","text":".] One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY baniY fulaAnK EiqaAlaAni","text_ar":"عَلَى بَنِى فُلَانٍ عِقَالَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"On the sons of such a one lies a poor-rate of two years."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.) And hence the saying of Aboo-Bekr,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawo manaEuwniY EiqaAlFA","text_ar":"لَوْ مَنَعُونِى عِقَالًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, O, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If they refused me a year's poor-rate:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, O:) and it is said that the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*a EiqaAlFA","text_ar":"اَخَذَ عِقَالًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"was used when the collector of the poor-rate took the camels themselves, not their price: (TA:) or Aboo-Bekr meant"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rope of the kind above mentioned;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, O, Msb;) for when one gave the poor-rate of his camels, he gave with them their"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euqul","text_ar":"عُقُل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, Msb:) or (Mgh, TA) he meant thereby a paltry thing, (Mgh, Msb, TA,) of the value of the [rope called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EqAl","text_ar":"عقال"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or he said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanaAqFA","text_ar":"عَنَاقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[“ a she-kid ”]; (Mgh, TA;) so accord. to Bkh, (Mgh,) and most others: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juday~FA","text_ar":"جُدَيًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[“ a little kid ”]. (Mgh, TA.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A young"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she-camel such as is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaluwS","text_ar":"قَلُوص"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqaAlu Almiy^iyna","text_ar":"عِقَالُ المِيِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The man of high rank who, when he has been made a prisoner, is ransomed with hundreds of camels."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","O","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n29988","headword_ar":"عُقَّالٌ","root":"Eql","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A limping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slight lameness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZalaEN","text_ar":"ظَلَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in copies of the S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalaEN","text_ar":"ضَلَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is said to signify the same, or correctly to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a natural crookedness"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (so in other copies of the S and in the O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which occurs in the legs of a beast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain disease in the hind leg of a beast, such that, when he goes along, he limps,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is slightly lame, for a while, after which he stretches forth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) accord. to A'Obeyd, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"peculiar to the horse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) but"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it mostly occurs in sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daA='N *uw Euq~aAlK","text_ar":"دَا=ءٌ ذُو عُقَّالٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A disease of which one will not be cured."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euq~aAlu AlkalaA^i","text_ar":"عُقَّالُ الكَلَاِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Three herbs that remain after having been cut,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which are the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEodaAnap","text_ar":"سَعْدَانَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hul~ab","text_ar":"حُلَّب"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quTobap","text_ar":"قُطْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqaAqiylu","text_ar":"عَقَاقِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [a pl.] of which the sing. is not mentioned, [perhaps pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euq~aAlN","text_ar":"عُقَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but in two senses a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqanoqalN","text_ar":"عَقَنْقَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portions"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a grape-vine"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that are raised and supported upon a trellis"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}